title: This Week’s Gridiron Matchups
text:
High school football games involving schools from Barbour County: 
All Games kickoff at 7 p.m. 
FRIDAY, Oct. 9 
WHO: Eufaula Tigers at Charles Henderson Trojans 
WHERE: at Veterans Memorial Stadium, Troy 
SERIES: Eufaula leads, 43-27 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Charles Henderson 42, Eufaula 14 
Records: Eufaula (5-1, 3-0); Charles Henderson (2-4, 1-2) 
COACHES: Bryan Moore (5-1 in first season at Eufaula); Brad McCoy (10-8 in second season at Charles Henderson) 
Noteworthy: This series has been streaky. Charles Henderson won three straight from 2007-09, Eufaula won the next three years, and Charles Henderson has won the last two, convincingly – 59-42 and 42-18. The series dates back to 1922 when Eufaula won 38-0. The Tigers hold the series’ edge, thanks to winning 10 straight from 1949-59, and six straight from 1984-89. 
WHO: Lakeside School Chiefs at Abbeville Christian Generals 
WHERE: at Generals Stadium, Abbeville 
SERIES: Lakeside leads, 23-12 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Lakeside 43, Abbeville Christian 21 
RECORDS: Lakeside School (4-2); Abbeville Christian (6-0) 
COACHES: Keith Jones (3-2 in first season at Lakeside); Ashley Carlisle (33-11 in fourth season at Abbeville Christian) 
Noteworthy: Lakeside had won five straight in the series from 2005-11 before losing two of the last three. The best game in the 35-year history came in 1992 when Lakeside captured a 28-20 double-overtime victory in Eufaula. The most lopsided game of the series was a 54-0 Lakeside win in 2010. 
WHO: Barbour County Jaguars at Brantley Bulldogs 
WHERE: at Brantley Field 
LAST MEETING: 2014, Brantley 62,, Barbour County 12 
RECORDS: Barbour County (0-7); Brantley (4-2) 
COACHES: Chris Reynolds (0-17 in second season at Barbour County); Ashley Kilcrease (27-6 in third season at Brantley) 
Noteworthy: In the previous 12 seasons, Brantley has won at least 10 games all but once (8-3 in 2010). The Bulldogs averaged 11.8 wins per seasons, winning Class 1A state championships in 2009 and 2012.
